      "stem_html": "<p>The following reaction involves an intramolecular Michael reaction followed by an intramolecular aldol reaction. Write both steps, and show their mechanisms.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc01ZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--488f9872c20283597cd8ec4f0822ceeba18f7aee/OChem_23_EC_028.jpg\" alt=\"A cyclopentenone ring with a 5-ethyl-6-methylhept-6-en-2-one side chain reacts with sodium hydroxide and ethanol to yield a product in which a cyclohexanone ring is fused with two cyclopentane rings.\">\n",
